      • getVariable

        <T> T getVariable(java.lang.String name)
        The flow may accumulate a lot of data during is life-cycle. The data can be accessed by "names". This method can be used to retrieve the flow data associated with the flow upto the point of invocation of this method.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the flow variable
        Returns:
        returns the value of the flow variable

      • getVariableAsString

        java.lang.String getVariableAsString(java.lang.String name)
        This is similar to getVariable(String name) except that the output will always be a String. For non-String objects, String.valueof would be used to compute the String value for the object.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the flow variable
        Returns:
        returns the string value of the flow variable

      • addFlowInfo

        boolean addFlowInfo(FlowInfo flowInfo)
        Data can be added to thfe flow at any time during it life-cycle. The data can be any object that implements FlowInfo. Ensure that FlowInfo#getIdentifier() returns a unique string.
        Parameters:
        flowInfo - the flow data to associate with the flow
